# IDStudio reverse proxy.
# - Public domain  → Caddy auto-provisions a Let's Encrypt certificate.
# - DOMAIN=localhost → Caddy serves HTTPS with its built-in internal CA.
# - DOMAIN=<bare IP> → internal CA cert; the global `default_sni` makes Caddy serve
#   that cert to clients which omit SNI (browsers omit SNI for raw IP addresses),
#   so an internal-only deployment reachable by IP still works over HTTPS.
# For production, optionally add a global `email {$ACME_EMAIL}` block for ACME notices.

{
	default_sni {$DOMAIN:localhost}
}

{$DOMAIN:localhost} {
	encode gzip
	reverse_proxy app:3000
}
